Edna Andradeâ€™s Twilight Wave (1973)

library(tidyverse)
library(gifski)
#defining the wave colors
colors<-c(
          "#dfe2db",
          "#d3d5d2",
          "#c4c3c1",
          "#b7b2b8",
          "#a79da5",
          "#91ad9f",
          "#a1b6af",
          "#b1c6bf",
          "#c6d6cc",
          "#dae1d9",
          "#e8ebe4"
          )

#making a circle dataframe
circle.pos<-data.frame(
  x<-sin(seq(0, 2*pi, length=100))*1/16,
  y<-cos(seq(0, 2*pi, length=100))*1/16
)

steps<-seq(0,2, by=1/32)

twilight.wave<-function(){
  for(i in steps){

  positions1<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-4+i)*pi,(2+i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.8
    )
  positions2<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-4.5-i)*pi,(1.5-i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.65
    )
  positions3<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-5+i)*pi,(1+i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.50
    )
  positions4<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-5.5-i)*pi,(.5-i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.35
    )
  positions5<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-6+i)*pi,(0+i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.2
    )
  positions6<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(1,sin(seq((-6.5-i)*pi,(-.5-i)*pi,
                  length.out = 100))*.08,
        1)-.05
    )
  positions7<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(.5,sin(seq((-7+i)*pi,(-1+i)*pi,
                   length.out = 100))*.08,
        .5)+.1
    )
  positions8<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(.5,sin(seq((-7.5-i)*pi,(-1.5-i)*pi,
                   length.out = 100))*.08,
        .5)+.25
    )
  positions9<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(.5,sin(seq((-8+i)*pi,(-2+i)*pi,
                   length.out = 100))*.08,
        .5)+.4
    )
  positions10<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(.25,sin(seq((-8.5-i)*pi,(-2.5-i)*pi,
                    length.out = 100))*.08,
        .25)+.55
    )
  positions11<-data.frame(
    y=c(-1,seq(-1,1, length.out=100),1),
    x=c(.3,sin(seq((-9+i)*pi,(-3+i)*pi,
                   length.out = 100))*.08,
        .3)+.7
    )

#get initial area the right color
  g<-ggplot()+ theme(panel.background =
                       element_rect(fill='#e8eadf',
                                    colour='white'),
                     panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
                     panel.grid.minor = element_blank())


  g<-g+
    geom_polygon(data=positions1, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[1])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions2, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[2])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions3, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[3])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions4, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[4])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions5, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[5])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions6, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[6])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions7, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[7])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions8, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[8])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions9, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[9])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions10, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[10])+
    geom_polygon(data=positions11, 
                 aes(x=x, y=y), 
                 fill=colors[11])+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y+5/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y-5/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y-10/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y+10/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y-15/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    geom_polygon(data=circle.pos,
                 aes(x=x, y=y+15/16),
                 fill="#ff9e3e")+
    coord_fixed()+
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-1,1), expand = c(0, 0)) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-1,1), expand = c(0, 0))+
    theme(axis.title.x=element_blank(),
          axis.text.x=element_blank(),
          axis.ticks.x=element_blank(),
          axis.title.y=element_blank(),
          axis.text.y=element_blank(),
          axis.ticks.y=element_blank())
  print(g)
  }
}



invisible(save_gif(twilight.wave(), "twilight.gif", delay = 0.1, progress = FALSE))  

knitr::include_graphics("twilight.gif")
